 Section 6(xvii) of the U.P. Imposition of Ceiling on Land Holdings Act, 1960, and rule 4(4) of the rules made thereunder are protected by Arts. 31A and 31B of the Constitution. [720C-D] (a)They are part of a scheme of land reform in U.P. and would therefore be protected from attack under Art. 31A.
 [720D] (b)The rule does not go beyond the powers conferred by the section read with s. 44 of the Act, and the Act is included to the Ninth Schedule to the Constitution. If a statutory rule is within the power conferred by a section of a statute protected by Art. 31B the rule cannot further be scrutinised under Arts. 14, 19 and 31. [720C] 
